  "intro": "Across more than fifteen years at Jahangirnagar University, complemented by part-time teaching at North South University and academic teaching experience in New Zealand, Dr. Snigdha has taught at both graduate and postgraduate levels across medical anthropology, gender and sexuality, political anthropology, urban anthropology, applied anthropology, and interdisciplinary social sciences. She also supervises MSS and MPhil research, particularly in the areas of gender, sexuality, medical anthropology, and marginalized communities",
